HEADWORD: Hydrocephaloid
<hw>Hy`dro*ceph"a*loid</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Hydrocephalus</ets> + <ets>-oid</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>Resembling hydrocephalus.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Hydrocephaloid affection</b></col> <fld>(Med.)</fld>,
<cd>the group of symptoms which follow exhausting diarrhea in young
children, resembling those of acute hydrocephalus, or tubercular
meningitis.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hydrocephalous</ent>⟦br⟧
